translated: Örn, Carl Elis Wilhelm, regimental physician, chief physician, Eksjö, b. 10/4/1894 in Karlstad to regimental physician Elis Ö. and Thérèse Uggla. Married on 28 m. Carin Nordstedt. Children: Torsten b. 1933. - Graduated from Karlstad Stud:-ex. in 1912, medical candidate in Uppsala in 1916, medical licentiate in Stockholm in 1922. Regimental assistant physician and acting assistant physician at Seraf:las medical clinic in 1917 and 1920, assistant physician at Saltsjöbaden's bathing institution in 1920-1921, second and acting first assistant physician at Karlstad hospital medical department in 1922-1924, first assistant physician there in 1924, assistant physician at Uppsala's medical and pediatric polyclinic, doctor at Uppsala's tuberculosis dispensary, and assistant at Uppsala's medical clinic in 1925-1926, acting hospital physician at Garn:-sjukh. in Eksjö's civilian department for internal patients in 1926-1929, hospital physician there in 1929 and chief physician since 1939, school physician at Eksjö grammar school in 1932, former physician at Stockholm's epidemic hospital in 1930 and at Crown Princess Lovisa's care institution in 1934. Battalion physician at Fik from 1925-1929, at Jönköping-Kalmar regiment from 1929-1939, regimental physician since 1939. Written works: papers on medical topics. RVO.
